			<div id="post-3959" class="hentry p1 post publish author-c4chaos category-dharma-practice y2011 m09 d30 h01">
				<h3 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.c4chaos.com/2011/09/response-to-brad-warners-annoyed-reaction-to-ken-wilbers-brain-waves/" title="Permalink to Response to Brad Warner&#8217;s Annoyed Reaction to Ken Wilber&#8217;s Brain Waves" rel="bookmark">Response to Brad Warner&#8217;s Annoyed Reaction to Ken Wilber&#8217;s Brain Waves</a></h3>
				<div class="entry-date"><abbr class="published" title="2011-09-30T08:15:51+0000">Friday, September 30th, 2011</abbr></div>
				<div class="entry-content">
<p>As I&#8217;ve obviously stated in the title of the this blog post, this is a response to Brad Warner&#8217;s article published on Suicide Girls blog. In that article he compared Ken Wilber stopping-his-brain-waves video to the art of street juggling. Since I&#8217;m the unnamed &#8220;Facebook friend&#8221; and &#8220;commenter&#8221; Brad referred to who posted the video [&hellip;]</p>
